<emphasis box="[269,391,1001,1021]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1029">
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Spreng." box="[269,387,1001,1021]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="26" pageNumber="1029" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selloi">Senecio selloi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[394,414,1001,1021]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1029">A.</emphasis>
plant. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[475,494,1001,1021]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1029">B.</emphasis>
steams at blooming.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="26.[168,776,1069,1429]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1029">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[206,336,1237,1261]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1029">Comments.</emphasis>
This is an infrequent species in the study area. It grows in full sunlight conditions in cracks on the summit. 
<taxonomicName box="[263,651,1304,1328]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="26" pageNumber="1029" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="grisebachii" variety="subincanus">
<emphasis box="[263,475,1304,1328]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1029">Senecio grisebachii</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[531,651,1304,1328]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1029">subincanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only variety of 
<taxonomicName box="[286,437,1338,1362]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="26" pageNumber="1029" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grisebachii">
<emphasis box="[286,437,1338,1362]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1029">S. grisebachii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that has been recorded in the region. It can be recognized by its tomentose, not glandular hairs and its pubescent achenes.
</paragraph>
